target.value: The number of beneficiaries that have been awarded investment grants and successfully imple-mented them.

actual.value:
615 received grant applications with a total investment amount of app. 14.5 Mio. EUR and the total grant amount applied for of app. 8.8 Mio. EUR. (Re-quest above the expectations and budget available)
269 beneficiaries contracted (Call 1 -79 out of 97 applications. call 2- 124 out of 141. call 3 – 61 out of 92. call 4 – 2 and in RT – 3) with total investment amount of 6.231.965 EUR and a total grant amount of 3.815.055 EUR
206 beneficiaries have completed their investments in line with the contracts and have submitted their Claim for Payments. Out of them. 186 beneficiaries are paid with a total investment amount of EUR 3.720.208 and with a total grant amount of EUR 2.415.220.
Out of 186 paid beneficiaries. 11% are women. 27% are young farmers and 49% of the investments were pre-financed by means of an external financial service provider.

target.value: Number of beneficiaries that have been awarded investment grants and successfully implemented them. of which at least 15% are women

actual.value: During 2016 a total of 330 investment grant applications have been submitted with a total investment amount of EUR 8 million and total grant amount of app. EUR 5 million applied for. Of the 330 applications. 47 are from Shkoder. 30 from Kukes. 26 from Diber. 27 from Elbasan. 28 from Berat and 172 from Korca. Out of these 31 (9%) have been submitted by women and 98 (30%) are young entrepreneurs. By the end of December 2016. 184 of the applications have been contracted with a total grant amount of EUR 2.456.000. So far 74 investments with a total grant amount of 979.000 EUR have been completed and payed. Out of these 13% of the beneficiaries are women. and 68% of the investments were pre-financed by means of an external financial service provider.

target.value: The share of grants that are used by farmers and MSMEs for diver-sification. both on-farm and off-farm (Diversification is defined as new products. MAPs and rural tourism).

actual.value: Out of the 330 investment grant applications received. 119 (36%) are for investments to be used for diversification defined as new products (70). MAPs (40). on-farm processing (9). Of the 74 completed investments. it is 16 (22%) that have been used for diversification. The preliminary survey conducted for the first 25 investment beneficiaries indicate that pro-duction has increased by 14% (fruits & nuts: 15%; small ruminants: 23%; MAPs: 9%). and that sales have increased by 13% (fruits & nuts: 15%; small ruminants: 21%; MAPs: 6%) from 2015 to 2016.

target.value: The number of VC groups/members organised under the existing agricultural associa-tions and cooperatives has in-creased in the programme re-gions.
The number of VC groups/members organised under the existing agricultural associa-tions and cooperatives has increased in the programme regions.

actual.value: The number of VC groups have increased from 78 to 108 (38%) and the members from 1.200 to 1.700 (42%). The 55 VC-AGs are well distributed within the regions. and it is envi-sioned that eventually more members will join the groups. and/or they will serve as inspira-tion for establishment of new groups. In all VC-AGs the members agree on common produc-tion practices and quality standards. and agreements are facilitated between producers and collectors and/or processors. The initiatives involve cooperation between public and private advisory services. producers and traders.
